<TITLE> Mugger in custody kills policeman </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 18 (bdnews24.com)  A mugger in police custody knifed to death a police sub-inspector and injured three other policemen in Bhairab of Kishoreganj district Wednesday night, police said. SI Mostafizur Rahman died on way to hospital. SI Mizanur Rahman and constable Ruhul Amin were sent to Dhaka Medical college Hospital while constable Abdul Kuddus received treatment at a local hotel. The mugger, identified by police as 'Mamun', managed to flee. Officer in charge of Bhairab Police Station Shahjahan Kabir told bdnews24.com police arrested Mamun in the evening. Immediately after the arrest, he escaped stabbing Kuddus and Amin. Two hours into the incident, Mostaf and Mizan arrested him in Monamara bridge area. They were coming to the police station on a motorcycle with the mugger when the mugger stabbed Mizanur first. He lost control of the motorcycle and all three fell on the road. Mamun then stabbed Mostafizur. Additional police and RAB were deployed in the area. Mamun, whose home is in Bhairabpur village, is a nephew of the president of Upazila BNP, police said. bdn
